  "prompt": "Do all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE?",
  "response": "Not all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE). While most modern smartphones released in the last decade do come equipped with Bluetooth 4.0 or later versions, older models and some budget or feature phones may not support it. Bluetooth 4.0 was introduced in 2010, and BLE is a feature of this version that allows for low-power wireless communication. \n\nIf you\u2019re looking to purchase a smartphone and want to ensure it has Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE, it's a good idea to check the specifications of the specific model you are considering.",
